      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(exec): expand leading ~ in workdir to home directory",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`exec` tool does not expand a leading `~` in `workdir`, then falls back to another directory and still executes the command, causing relative commands to run from the wrong location.\n\n**Root cause:** `resolveWorkdir()` in `src/agents/bash-tools.shared.ts` passed `workdir` directly to `statSync()` without expanding `~`/`~/` to the user's home directory.\n\n**Fix:** Add leading tilde expansion at the top of `resolveWorkdir()` before the stat check, using `os.homedir()`.\n\nFixes #94434\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n**Behavior addressed**: `resolveWorkdir(\"~/nonexistent/path\")` now expands `~/` to the home directory before the stat check, instead of treating the tilde as a literal path component.\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: Linux x86_64 (kernel 4.19.112), Node v24.13.1, OpenClaw worktree at `6db0fb3197`\n\n**Exact steps or command run after fix**:\n\n```bash\nnode --import tsx -e '\nimport { resolveWorkdir } from \"./src/agents/bash-tools.shared.ts\";\nconst w = [];\nconsole.log(\"~/path →\", resolveWorkdir(\"~/nonexistent\", w), \"| warnings:\", w.length > 0 ? \"yes\" : \"no\");\nw.length = 0;\nconsole.log(\"~ →\", resolveWorkdir(\"~\", w), \"| warnings:\", w.length > 0 ? \"yes\" : \"no\");\nw.length = 0;\nconsole.log(\"/tmp →\", resolveWorkdir(\"/tmp\", w), \"| warnings:\", w.length > 0 ? \"yes\" : \"no\");\n'\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n\n```\n~/path → /home/0668001315/nonexistent | warnings: yes\n~ → /home/0668001315 | warnings: no\n/tmp → /tmp | warnings: no\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: When a tool call passes `workdir: \"~/path\"`, the tilde is expanded to the user's home directory before the stat check — if the expanded path exists it is used directly; if not, the fallback warning now shows the expanded path (not the literal `~`).\n\n**What was not tested**: Full end-to-end exec tool invocation through Gateway (requires a live agent session with a model that emits `workdir: \"~...\"`).\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n```\n$ pnpm test src/agents/bash-tools.test.ts\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  37 passed (37)\n```\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes`)\n- `exec.workdir` with leading `~`/`~/` now expands to home directory instead of failing\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`No`)\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`No`)\n- Tilde expansion only affects paths starting with `~`; uses `os.homedir()` which has no side effects\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n- Edge case where homedir() returns an unexpected path\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n- If the expanded path does not exist, the existing fallback mechanism still applies\n- The fix only triggers on leading `~` or `~/`, leaving all other path forms unchanged\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n- Maintainer review\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-94434-exec-workdir-tilde-expansion",
